1
00:00:07,491 --> 00:00:10,455
<b>(Episode 11)</b>

2
00:00:32,349 --> 00:00:34,080
<b>Hello, Director.</b>

3
00:00:34,084 --> 00:00:35,815
<b>Nice to meet you.</b>

4
00:00:36,286 --> 00:00:38,880
<b>I already heard from Tae Eun.</b>

5
00:00:38,889 --> 00:00:40,520
<b>Is this your first time here?</b>

6
00:00:40,524 --> 00:00:42,915
<b>Yes, it's my first time.</b>

7
00:00:42,959 --> 00:00:45,285
<b>Please, let's go inside.</b>

8
00:00:46,296 --> 00:00:49,795
<b>May I ask you for the reason?</b>

9
00:00:50,133 --> 00:00:54,270
<b>You never visited us for the last eight years.</b>

10
00:00:54,271 --> 00:00:57,135
<b>Why did you suddenly want to visit?</b>

11
00:00:59,943 --> 00:01:02,035
<b>I wanted to check...</b>

12
00:01:07,050 --> 00:01:10,485
<b>that he was stuck in there...</b>

13
00:01:11,054 --> 00:01:13,755
<b>with no rights whatsoever.</b>

14
00:01:15,392 --> 00:01:16,960
<b>I wanted to know...</b>

15
00:01:16,960 --> 00:01:18,460
<b>(Quarantine Treatment Room 1: Moon Seong Ho)</b>

16
00:01:18,462 --> 00:01:20,425
<b>that there was nothing he could do.</b>

17
00:01:21,665 --> 00:01:24,865
<b>And I also wanted to know...</b>

18
00:01:25,302 --> 00:01:27,665
<b>that I'd never lose someone again because of him.</b>

19
00:01:32,642 --> 00:01:36,740
<b>This is the first and the last time I'm doing this favor for you.</b>

20
00:01:36,746 --> 00:01:38,910
<b>Going there doesn't do you any good.</b>

21
00:01:38,915 --> 00:01:40,615
<b>I know.</b>

22
00:01:40,984 --> 00:01:44,150
<b>I just wanted to check that it really wasn't him.</b>

23
00:01:44,154 --> 00:01:46,280
<b>I know what you're thinking.</b>

24
00:01:46,289 --> 00:01:48,690
<b>It's not true. That won't ever happen again.</b>

25
00:01:48,692 --> 00:01:51,385
<b>You saw him locked up.</b>

26
00:01:52,429 --> 00:01:54,530
<b>Ha Jin is a celebrity.</b>

27
00:01:54,531 --> 00:01:56,760
<b>She may have some obsessed fans.</b>

28
00:01:56,766 --> 00:01:58,960
<b>She can be more careful from now on.</b>

29
00:01:58,969 --> 00:02:01,695
<b>So don't take it too seriously.</b>

30
00:02:03,507 --> 00:02:06,065
<b>I thought the same thing eight years ago.</b>

31
00:02:07,511 --> 00:02:09,675
<b>I thought it was just a coincidence.</b>

32
00:02:10,180 --> 00:02:11,945
<b>I thought it wasn't a big deal.</b>

33
00:02:26,329 --> 00:02:28,355
<b>Did you wait for long?</b>

34
00:02:31,468 --> 00:02:33,365
<b>I saw him at the convenience store.</b>

35
00:02:33,970 --> 00:02:36,100
<b>Are these silver?</b>

36
00:02:36,106 --> 00:02:37,865
<b>Doesn't it look nice?</b>

37
00:02:39,042 --> 00:02:40,310
<b>Yes.</b>

38
00:02:40,310 --> 00:02:42,075
<b>I saw him at a cafe.</b>

39
00:02:44,114 --> 00:02:47,775
<b>I saw him many times but thought nothing of it.</b>

40
00:02:48,018 --> 00:02:50,445
<b>I thought it was understandable since he lived nearby.</b>

41
00:02:50,987 --> 00:02:52,885
<b>Had I...</b>

42
00:02:53,890 --> 00:02:56,615
<b>suspected him at least once...</b>

43
00:02:57,227 --> 00:03:00,285
<b>Had I taken it more seriously, I would've been able to stop it.</b>

44
00:03:00,630 --> 00:03:02,295
<b>I'm the reason...</b>

45
00:03:03,033 --> 00:03:04,825
<b>Seo Yeon died.</b>

46
00:03:07,470 --> 00:03:11,665
<b>I don't think I'll be able to live if the same thing happened again.</b>

47
00:03:13,410 --> 00:03:15,535
<b>I can't lose Ha Jin.</b>

48
00:03:36,933 --> 00:03:37,930
<b>Are you looking for something?</b>

49
00:03:37,934 --> 00:03:39,560
<b>I can't find the other one.</b>

50
00:03:39,569 --> 00:03:41,100
<b>Didn't you keep them together?</b>

51
00:03:41,104 --> 00:03:43,500
<b>I thought I did, but I can't find one of them.</b>

52
00:03:43,506 --> 00:03:46,805
<b>I had purposely set them aside for today's meeting.</b>

53
00:03:46,943 --> 00:03:49,875
<b>Maybe it got snatched by one of your clothes.</b>

54
00:03:49,946 --> 00:03:51,610
<b>Look carefully.</b>

55
00:03:51,615 --> 00:03:53,675
<b>Are you sure you didn't wear it?</b>

56
00:03:53,850 --> 00:03:55,575
<b>Not in a million years.</b>

57
00:03:56,620 --> 00:03:58,385
<b>Gosh.</b>

58
00:04:03,260 --> 00:04:05,285
<b>This would've been perfect.</b>

59
00:04:29,286 --> 00:04:31,150
<b>You're here early.</b>

60
00:04:31,154 --> 00:04:32,915
<b>Hello.</b>

61
00:04:32,989 --> 00:04:34,120
<b>Hello.</b>

62
00:04:34,124 --> 00:04:37,555
<b>- Hello. Take this first. - What?</b>

63
00:04:39,629 --> 00:04:41,090
<b>If you're hesitant about saying something, then don't.</b>

64
00:04:41,097 --> 00:04:42,960
<b>Just answer their questions. Don't say anything unnecessary.</b>

65
00:04:42,966 --> 00:04:44,600
<b>- Okay. - Should I wait in the car...</b>

66
00:04:44,601 --> 00:04:45,960
<b>around 9pm?</b>

67
00:04:45,969 --> 00:04:47,730
<b>- Yes. - That's okay.</b>

68
00:04:47,737 --> 00:04:49,935
<b>I'll drop her home.</b>

69
00:04:51,107 --> 00:04:53,065
<b>That'd be great.</b>

70
00:04:54,110 --> 00:04:56,835
<b>- Let's go. - Okay.</b>

71
00:05:04,187 --> 00:05:07,190
<b>You two look great together. Right?</b>

72
00:05:07,190 --> 00:05:08,755
<b>I guess.</b>

73
00:05:08,825 --> 00:05:10,720
<b>Do you have a lot of time today?</b>

74
00:05:10,727 --> 00:05:13,020
<b>I'd like to ask you every single question I have.</b>

75
00:05:13,029 --> 00:05:14,795
<b>Sure.</b>

76
00:05:15,198 --> 00:05:18,600
<b>I always study beforehand,</b>

77
00:05:18,601 --> 00:05:21,465
<b>but I get stuck every time I write my scripts.</b>

78
00:05:21,971 --> 00:05:24,640
<b>Let's drink. They seem busy.</b>

79
00:05:24,641 --> 00:05:26,505
<b>Okay.</b>

80
00:05:26,676 --> 00:05:27,940
<b>Look at this.</b>

81
00:05:27,944 --> 00:05:30,440
<b>These are all the questions I have for you.</b>

82
00:05:30,447 --> 00:05:32,005
<b>I see.</b>

83
00:05:33,550 --> 00:05:35,675
<b>I saw your movie.</b>

84
00:05:35,985 --> 00:05:37,845
<b>I see.</b>

85
00:05:38,221 --> 00:05:41,550
<b>You looked beautiful from the opening scene.</b>

86
00:05:41,558 --> 00:05:43,185
<b>I liked your acting as well.</b>

87
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:45,485
<b>Really?</b>

88
00:05:45,795 --> 00:05:47,525
<b>Let me be honest.</b>

89
00:05:47,897 --> 00:05:49,830
<b>I was a bit hesitant at first.</b>

90
00:05:49,833 --> 00:05:52,230
<b>But after watching it, I was sure.</b>

91
00:05:52,235 --> 00:05:55,935
<b>I realized I could count on you.</b>

92
00:05:56,439 --> 00:05:59,540
<b>Thank you for saying that. I'll do my best.</b>

93
00:05:59,542 --> 00:06:01,040
<b>Okay.</b>

94
00:06:01,044 --> 00:06:03,410
<b>Let's eat while we chat.</b>

95
00:06:03,413 --> 00:06:05,110
<b>Our food was served a while ago.</b>

96
00:06:05,115 --> 00:06:07,510
<b>I'm sorry for blabbering on and on.</b>

97
00:06:07,517 --> 00:06:09,875
<b>Enjoy your meal.</b>

98
00:06:10,019 --> 00:06:12,680
<b>Ha Jin, this is really delicious. Try it.</b>

99
00:06:12,689 --> 00:06:14,355
<b>Okay.</b>

100
00:06:15,425 --> 00:06:17,090
<b>When Ha Na was young,</b>

101
00:06:17,093 --> 00:06:20,160
<b>she didn't know she was allergic to shrimp...</b>

102
00:06:20,163 --> 00:06:22,690
<b>and thought they always stung.</b>

103
00:06:22,699 --> 00:06:25,660
<b>She always thought it was strange but continued to eat them.</b>

104
00:06:25,668 --> 00:06:27,600
<b>In the end, she was carried to the ER...</b>

105
00:06:27,604 --> 00:06:30,000
<b>but still didn't know it was because of the shrimp.</b>

106
00:06:30,006 --> 00:06:31,140
<b>Isn't that funny?</b>

107
00:06:31,141 --> 00:06:33,905
<b>Yes, it is.</b>

108
00:06:37,180 --> 00:06:39,275
<b>You can't have shrimp.</b>

109
00:06:42,118 --> 00:06:44,520
<b>That was shrimp? I didn't know.</b>

110
00:06:44,521 --> 00:06:46,180
<b>What is it? Are you allergic?</b>

111
00:06:46,189 --> 00:06:48,120
<b>Yes, my throat swells.</b>

112
00:06:48,124 --> 00:06:50,320
<b>I break out in hives as well. It takes me a while to get better.</b>

113
00:06:50,326 --> 00:06:52,360
<b>I'm so sorry.</b>

114
00:06:52,362 --> 00:06:54,825
<b>It could've been dangerous.</b>

115
00:06:54,831 --> 00:06:56,795
<b>I'm glad.</b>

116
00:06:56,833 --> 00:07:00,470
<b>Your boyfriend knows everything about you.</b>

117
00:07:00,470 --> 00:07:02,035
<b>Lucky you.</b>

118
00:07:02,839 --> 00:07:05,235
<b>We should eat this.</b>

119
00:07:05,942 --> 00:07:07,905
<b>How did you know?</b>

120
00:07:07,944 --> 00:07:10,135
<b>Have I told you before?</b>

121
00:07:13,249 --> 00:07:15,910
<b>Please excuse me. I need to go to the restroom.</b>

122
00:07:15,919 --> 00:07:17,685
<b>Sure.</b>

123
00:07:22,592 --> 00:07:25,420
<b>It's probably best for her to practice reading the news...</b>

124
00:07:25,428 --> 00:07:26,930
<b>as soon as possible, right?</b>

125
00:07:26,930 --> 00:07:28,525
<b>Yes.</b>

126
00:07:29,499 --> 00:07:32,800
<b>But then again, he'll help you with that.</b>

127
00:07:32,802 --> 00:07:34,830
<b>I have nothing to worry about, right?</b>

128
00:07:34,838 --> 00:07:38,465
<b>Of course. I bet he'll be very strict.</b>

129
00:07:39,843 --> 00:07:43,575
<b>Excuse me. I need to take this.</b>

130
00:07:50,420 --> 00:07:51,850
<b>Let's drink.</b>

131
00:07:51,855 --> 00:07:53,445
<b>Okay.</b>

132
00:08:00,196 --> 00:08:01,995
<b>Are you confident?</b>

133
00:08:02,632 --> 00:08:04,665
<b>This drama won't be easy.</b>

134
00:08:05,168 --> 00:08:07,130
<b>I'm not confident, but if I try my...</b>

135
00:08:07,136 --> 00:08:08,795
<b>You're not?</b>

136
00:08:09,172 --> 00:08:10,965
<b>Then you shouldn't do it.</b>

137
00:08:11,107 --> 00:08:13,135
<b>You should take work seriously.</b>

138
00:08:13,943 --> 00:08:14,940
<b>Sorry?</b>

139
00:08:14,944 --> 00:08:18,075
<b>Writer Hwang wanted to cast you, so I said okay.</b>

140
00:08:18,481 --> 00:08:20,305
<b>But I'm not happy with this.</b>

141
00:08:21,050 --> 00:08:25,145
<b>I want the lead actress to be elegant.</b>

142
00:08:26,055 --> 00:08:28,115
<b>But you're...</b>

143
00:08:28,324 --> 00:08:30,315
<b>You probably know it too.</b>

144
00:08:31,027 --> 00:08:32,755
<b>You're far from it.</b>

145
00:08:40,904 --> 00:08:43,035
<b>Let's be honest.</b>

146
00:08:43,072 --> 00:08:46,765
<b>Do you think you're fit for the role as a news anchor?</b>

147
00:08:48,845 --> 00:08:50,735
<b>Aren't you embarrassed?</b>

148
00:08:50,847 --> 00:08:54,615
<b>I know you picked this because of your boyfriend.</b>

149
00:08:55,718 --> 00:08:59,815
<b>But then again, I guess it's a talent to date competent men.</b>

150
00:09:02,091 --> 00:09:03,785
<b>I think...</b>

151
00:09:05,094 --> 00:09:07,385
<b>you're out of line.</b>

152
00:09:08,064 --> 00:09:09,795
<b>That's great.</b>

153
00:09:09,999 --> 00:09:11,695
<b>You don't like me, right?</b>

154
00:09:11,901 --> 00:09:15,235
<b>Then let's not waste any energy and just put an end to this.</b>

155
00:09:15,271 --> 00:09:18,540
<b>Writer Hwang is just infatuated with Anchor Lee.</b>

156
00:09:18,541 --> 00:09:21,470
<b>But she'll come to her senses after hearing you read the script.</b>

157
00:09:21,477 --> 00:09:23,740
<b>So put an end to this.</b>

158
00:09:23,746 --> 00:09:26,775
<b>Say that your schedule is busy or that you're feeling sick.</b>

159
00:09:27,450 --> 00:09:29,115
<b>Do you understand?</b>

160
00:09:44,867 --> 00:09:48,935
<b>I'm sorry. It was urgent.</b>

161
00:09:50,907 --> 00:09:53,035
<b>What were we talking about again?</b>

162
00:09:53,209 --> 00:09:56,110
<b>Right. We were talking about how excellent of a teacher...</b>

163
00:09:56,112 --> 00:09:59,205
<b>you'd be for her.</b>

164
00:09:59,849 --> 00:10:02,980
<b>Of course. I'm going to do my best.</b>

165
00:10:02,986 --> 00:10:04,720
<b>You'll be taken aback during the script reading...</b>

166
00:10:04,721 --> 00:10:06,320
<b>by how realistic she sounds.</b>

167
00:10:06,322 --> 00:10:09,550
<b>Oh, my! I'm already looking forward to this.</b>

168
00:10:09,559 --> 00:10:13,220
<b>By the way, she didn't win this role...</b>

169
00:10:13,229 --> 00:10:15,160
<b>because of our relationship, did she?</b>

170
00:10:15,164 --> 00:10:16,855
<b>Not at all.</b>

171
00:10:18,001 --> 00:10:19,400
<b>I'm just worried...</b>

172
00:10:19,402 --> 00:10:22,370
<b>that people might think she got this role...</b>

173
00:10:22,372 --> 00:10:23,940
<b>because of her boyfriend.</b>

174
00:10:23,940 --> 00:10:26,670
<b>Not at all. That's absurd.</b>

175
00:10:26,676 --> 00:10:28,510
<b>We wouldn't do that.</b>

176
00:10:28,511 --> 00:10:30,040
<b>After all, she's the one who'll be acting.</b>

177
00:10:30,046 --> 00:10:33,505
<b>Right? I guess that was unnecessary to ask.</b>

178
00:10:33,616 --> 00:10:34,880
<b>Those who think such foolish thoughts...</b>

179
00:10:34,884 --> 00:10:36,050
<b>are the weird ones.</b>

180
00:10:36,052 --> 00:10:37,420
<b>Of course.</b>

181
00:10:37,420 --> 00:10:39,850
<b>We shouldn't deal with scumbags like them.</b>

182
00:10:39,856 --> 00:10:41,615
<b>Right?</b>

183
00:10:41,624 --> 00:10:43,215
<b>Right.</b>

184
00:10:43,660 --> 00:10:47,385
<b>Ha Jin, don't be hurt by such rumors, okay?</b>

185
00:10:47,530 --> 00:10:49,125
<b>Okay.</b>

186
00:11:00,109 --> 00:11:02,905
<b>Can you buy me a can of beer?</b>

187
00:11:03,913 --> 00:11:06,905
<b>You drank a lot of wine earlier.</b>

188
00:11:07,316 --> 00:11:09,415
<b>Just one can.</b>

189
00:11:09,752 --> 00:11:12,485
<b>It's just that I feel so frustrated.</b>

190
00:11:13,189 --> 00:11:15,585
<b>Just buy me one can of beer.</b>

191
00:11:28,771 --> 00:11:30,535
<b>Thank you.</b>

192
00:11:47,256 --> 00:11:49,055
<b>Does that hit the spot?</b>

193
00:11:49,592 --> 00:11:51,385
<b>A bit.</b>

194
00:11:54,997 --> 00:11:56,555
<b>Here.</b>

195
00:12:06,542 --> 00:12:09,275
<b>I'm going to get off.</b>

196
00:13:02,165 --> 00:13:04,025
<b>Are you all right?</b>

197
00:13:05,668 --> 00:13:07,865
<b>Why did you drink so much?</b>

198
00:13:07,870 --> 00:13:10,195
<b>You heard everything earlier, didn't you?</b>

199
00:13:11,641 --> 00:13:14,035
<b>You heard everything earlier.</b>

200
00:13:15,711 --> 00:13:19,045
<b>The conversation between the director and me.</b>

201
00:13:21,818 --> 00:13:25,945
<b>Not everything. I caught a few sentences.</b>

202
00:13:27,056 --> 00:13:28,490
<b>But why are you speaking casually to me now?</b>

203
00:13:28,491 --> 00:13:30,390
<b>It's about time that we did.</b>

204
00:13:30,393 --> 00:13:33,655
<b>Until when do I have to address as Anchor Lee?</b>

205
00:13:33,830 --> 00:13:35,330
<b>Is this the alcohol talking?</b>

206
00:13:35,331 --> 00:13:37,795
<b>If you think it's unfair, you can talk to me casually too.</b>

207
00:13:44,574 --> 00:13:47,105
<b>Is that what you think too?</b>

208
00:13:48,811 --> 00:13:51,275
<b>Do I look cheap?</b>

209
00:13:52,915 --> 00:13:54,875
<b>Am I that awful?</b>

210
00:13:56,752 --> 00:13:59,745
<b>Do you have the same opinion of me as the director?</b>

211
00:14:00,690 --> 00:14:02,520
<b>Director, my foot.</b>

212
00:14:02,525 --> 00:14:05,025
<b>He's such a scumbag.</b>

213
00:14:05,561 --> 00:14:07,360
<b>He couldn't say anything in front of the writer,</b>

214
00:14:07,363 --> 00:14:09,855
<b>but he threatened an actress behind the writer.</b>

215
00:14:09,932 --> 00:14:12,325
<b>Why would you care about a scumbag like that?</b>

216
00:14:13,703 --> 00:14:16,235
<b>You said you really wanted to be in that drama.</b>

217
00:14:16,539 --> 00:14:18,335
<b>Then, you should be in it.</b>

218
00:14:18,641 --> 00:14:20,905
<b>Isn't going after what you want your thing?</b>

219
00:14:23,379 --> 00:14:25,205
<b>Can an anchor...</b>

220
00:14:26,449 --> 00:14:28,975
<b>badmouth someone like that?</b>

221
00:14:30,019 --> 00:14:31,585
<b>Why not?</b>

222
00:14:32,355 --> 00:14:35,285
<b>I'm really good at badmouthing people.</b>

223
00:14:39,729 --> 00:14:43,255
<b>There's no other way. I give up.</b>

224
00:14:43,966 --> 00:14:45,330
<b>You'll give up on the drama?</b>

225
00:14:45,334 --> 00:14:47,670
<b>No, I'll be in the drama.</b>

226
00:14:47,670 --> 00:14:49,900
<b>I must do it out of spite if I have to.</b>

227
00:14:49,906 --> 00:14:52,800
<b>Not the drama. I give up on speaking casually to you.</b>

228
00:14:52,808 --> 00:14:55,605
<b>I won't do it, so you don't get to talk to me casually.</b>

229
00:14:55,778 --> 00:14:58,445
<b>It makes my heart flutter, so I can't have that.</b>

230
00:15:00,983 --> 00:15:02,645
<b>And...</b>

231
00:15:03,152 --> 00:15:05,615
<b>don't blame me later.</b>

232
00:15:07,023 --> 00:15:10,485
<b>You brought this upon yourself.</b>

233
00:15:35,384 --> 00:15:37,015
<b>What is it?</b>

234
00:15:37,553 --> 00:15:39,615
<b>We can't do this.</b>

235
00:15:40,156 --> 00:15:42,185
<b>Why not?</b>

236
00:15:43,426 --> 00:15:45,285
<b>We'll regret it.</b>

237
00:15:46,662 --> 00:15:48,855
<b>I won't regret it.</b>

238
00:15:57,106 --> 00:15:59,135
<b>No, you will.</b>

239
00:16:00,810 --> 00:16:03,375
<b>Perhaps, you'll regret more than me.</b>

240
00:16:12,221 --> 00:16:14,755
<b>Gosh, why won't she call?</b>

241
00:16:19,996 --> 00:16:23,725
<b>What? I told you to call me before you got here.</b>

242
00:16:24,500 --> 00:16:27,095
<b>How did the meeting go? Did you do well?</b>

243
00:16:27,703 --> 00:16:28,930
<b>Why are you quiet?</b>

244
00:16:28,938 --> 00:16:30,370
<b>Did the meeting go well?</b>

245
00:16:30,373 --> 00:16:32,100
<b>Yes? Hello?</b>

246
00:16:32,108 --> 00:16:35,235
<b>Hello? Excuse me.</b>

247
00:16:37,980 --> 00:16:40,610
<b>What on earth happened?</b>

248
00:16:40,616 --> 00:16:41,880
<b>You reek of alcohol.</b>

249
00:16:41,884 --> 00:16:44,150
<b>Ha Jin, did you get drunk and cause trouble?</b>

250
00:16:44,153 --> 00:16:46,620
<b>Is that why you look sad?</b>

251
00:16:46,622 --> 00:16:48,715
<b>I didn't cause trouble.</b>

252
00:16:48,724 --> 00:16:50,120
<b>You did. I can tell.</b>

253
00:16:50,126 --> 00:16:51,390
<b>How did you mess it up?</b>

254
00:16:51,394 --> 00:16:55,095
<b>Don't tell me you got excited and overly friendly with them.</b>

255
00:16:57,600 --> 00:16:58,960
<b>You did. That's what you did.</b>

256
00:16:58,968 --> 00:17:00,430
<b>How will you fix this now?</b>

257
00:17:00,436 --> 00:17:02,000
<b>Seriously. You're making this very difficult for me.</b>

258
00:17:02,004 --> 00:17:04,800
<b>What if they say no and reject you?</b>

259
00:17:04,807 --> 00:17:06,800
<b>Why not? Why can't I do it?</b>

260
00:17:06,809 --> 00:17:08,140
<b>Why can't it be me?</b>

261
00:17:08,144 --> 00:17:09,910
<b>You can't do it? Did they already reject you?</b>

262
00:17:09,912 --> 00:17:12,540
<b>- Then, why was he nice to me? - Nice to you?</b>

263
00:17:12,548 --> 00:17:15,080
<b>He should have let me eat that shrimp.</b>

264
00:17:15,084 --> 00:17:16,150
<b>Shrimp?</b>

265
00:17:16,152 --> 00:17:20,385
<b>He took care of me, sided with me, and acted cool for no good reason.</b>

266
00:17:20,523 --> 00:17:22,390
<b>Cool? What did you say?</b>

267
00:17:22,391 --> 00:17:23,850
<b>Forget it.</b>

268
00:17:23,859 --> 00:17:26,990
<b>I don't want him, either. Tell him I don't want him.</b>

269
00:17:26,996 --> 00:17:29,290
<b>Weren't we talking about the drama?</b>

270
00:17:29,298 --> 00:17:31,100
<b>- Get out. - Hey.</b>

271
00:17:31,100 --> 00:17:33,165
<b>Get out!</b>

272
00:17:33,369 --> 00:17:36,200
<b>I don't want you. Gosh, I don't want this either.</b>

273
00:17:36,205 --> 00:17:37,765
<b>Goodness.</b>

274
00:17:39,008 --> 00:17:41,205
<b>Unbelievable.</b>

275
00:18:50,412 --> 00:18:51,440
<b>Aren't you hungry?</b>

276
00:18:51,447 --> 00:18:54,180
<b>There's a famous sushi restaurant nearby. Should we get some?</b>

277
00:18:54,183 --> 00:18:56,975
<b>I'm tired. Let's eat at home.</b>

278
00:18:56,986 --> 00:18:58,520
<b>Okay.</b>

279
00:18:58,521 --> 00:19:00,945
<b>You're not asking about Anchor Lee today.</b>

280
00:19:00,956 --> 00:19:02,320
<b>Whenever you came to do a radio show,</b>

281
00:19:02,324 --> 00:19:04,855
<b>you would think about calling him.</b>

282
00:19:06,729 --> 00:19:08,490
<b>Something happened between you two, right?</b>

283
00:19:08,497 --> 00:19:09,930
<b>What is it?</b>

284
00:19:09,932 --> 00:19:12,925
<b>Nothing happened. I'm just tired today.</b>

285
00:19:19,108 --> 00:19:20,370
<b>Yes, I just came down.</b>

286
00:19:20,376 --> 00:19:22,175
<b>- Where are you? - What are you doing?</b>

287
00:19:25,447 --> 00:19:28,075
<b>I'm in the lobby on the first floor. Where?</b>

288
00:19:29,218 --> 00:19:30,210
<b>What is this?</b>

289
00:19:30,219 --> 00:19:32,785
<b>You said nothing happened. Why are we hiding?</b>

290
00:19:33,622 --> 00:19:35,020
<b>Right.</b>

291
00:19:35,024 --> 00:19:37,915
<b>Why did I hide? I didn't do anything wrong.</b>

292
00:19:39,128 --> 00:19:41,790
<b>What about Mr. Jo? I thought the three of us were meeting.</b>

293
00:19:41,797 --> 00:19:42,890
<b>He'll be back soon.</b>

294
00:19:42,898 --> 00:19:44,500
<b>I told him to pay for the meal since he's late.</b>

295
00:19:44,500 --> 00:19:46,125
<b>So order something expensive.</b>

296
00:19:46,502 --> 00:19:48,170
<b>You did something wrong.</b>

297
00:19:48,170 --> 00:19:49,300
<b>When you met the writer and the director,</b>

298
00:19:49,305 --> 00:19:51,170
<b>did you mess up in front of Anchor Lee?</b>

299
00:19:51,173 --> 00:19:52,700
<b>Mess up?</b>

300
00:19:52,708 --> 00:19:55,105
<b>I didn't do anything wrong.</b>

301
00:19:56,345 --> 00:19:57,680
<b>Right.</b>

302
00:19:57,680 --> 00:20:00,210
<b>Why must I avoid him? I didn't do anything wrong.</b>

303
00:20:00,216 --> 00:20:03,015
<b>I can just say hello to him.</b>

304
00:20:03,085 --> 00:20:04,780
<b>We can surely exchange greetings.</b>

305
00:20:04,787 --> 00:20:07,620
<b>I'm not sure if I'll be of any help in writing the article.</b>

306
00:20:07,623 --> 00:20:09,190
<b>Schizophrenia isn't my area of expertise.</b>

307
00:20:09,191 --> 00:20:11,560
<b>You'll be just advising him.</b>

308
00:20:11,560 --> 00:20:13,760
<b>But make it sound as difficult as you can.</b>

309
00:20:13,762 --> 00:20:15,395
<b>I want him to suffer a bit.</b>

310
00:20:15,631 --> 00:20:17,325
<b>Let's go say hi.</b>

311
00:20:17,499 --> 00:20:19,065
<b>What?</b>

312
00:20:28,978 --> 00:20:31,410
<b>What brings you here, Doctor Yoo?</b>

313
00:20:31,413 --> 00:20:33,805
<b>Hi, Ha Jin.</b>

314
00:20:33,816 --> 00:20:34,880
<b>It's been a while.</b>

315
00:20:34,883 --> 00:20:37,510
<b>My gosh. It's been so long.</b>

316
00:20:37,519 --> 00:20:40,245
<b>I had no idea that I would run into you here.</b>

317
00:20:41,757 --> 00:20:44,290
<b>By the way, do you know each other?</b>

318
00:20:44,293 --> 00:20:46,585
<b>Why are you guys together?</b>

319
00:20:47,630 --> 00:20:50,030
<b>I'm sorry. I'm late.</b>

320
00:20:50,032 --> 00:20:52,360
<b>Hello. I've heard a lot about you.</b>

321
00:20:52,368 --> 00:20:54,570
<b>I didn't know it was possible for Jeong Hoon to have any friends.</b>

322
00:20:54,570 --> 00:20:56,495
<b>You're his only friend, right?</b>

323
00:20:56,739 --> 00:20:58,335
<b>"Friends"?</b>

324
00:20:58,540 --> 00:21:01,135
<b>Doctor Yoo and Anchor Lee?</b>

325
00:21:01,744 --> 00:21:04,905
<b>- Goodness, hello. - Hello.</b>

326
00:21:04,913 --> 00:21:07,280
<b>Are we all eating together?</b>

327
00:21:07,283 --> 00:21:09,010
<b>Oh, no. We aren't.</b>

328
00:21:09,018 --> 00:21:11,645
<b>If I'm not too much of a nuisance, may I go with you?</b>

329
00:21:13,088 --> 00:21:15,515
<b>I'd like to ask something too.</b>

330
00:21:24,233 --> 00:21:27,365
<b>Doctor Yoo was here to give advice for my article.</b>

331
00:21:28,637 --> 00:21:30,100
<b>I took on a new report...</b>

332
00:21:30,105 --> 00:21:32,970
<b>on crimes committed by schizophrenic patients.</b>

333
00:21:32,975 --> 00:21:34,905
<b>Oh, I see.</b>

334
00:21:35,644 --> 00:21:37,735
<b>But it doesn't look so great.</b>

335
00:21:38,247 --> 00:21:39,840
<b>I wouldn't have come if I had known.</b>

336
00:21:39,848 --> 00:21:43,315
<b>Exactly. You shouldn't have. You're very slow.</b>

337
00:21:45,354 --> 00:21:48,020
<b>Excuse me. I'd like three sushi A sets for that table...</b>

338
00:21:48,023 --> 00:21:49,650
<b>- and three sets for us. - Okay.</b>

339
00:21:49,658 --> 00:21:52,020
<b>Three for us? Are we expecting someone else?</b>

340
00:21:52,027 --> 00:21:54,390
<b>No, I just like sushi a lot.</b>

341
00:21:54,396 --> 00:21:56,930
<b>Why? Is this your 1st time seeing someone eat 2 sushi meals?</b>

342
00:21:56,932 --> 00:21:58,400
<b>Yes, it's my first time.</b>

343
00:21:58,400 --> 00:22:01,365
<b>My girlfriend can't even finish one.</b>

344
00:22:01,503 --> 00:22:04,170
<b>She must eat very little.</b>

345
00:22:04,173 --> 00:22:07,440
<b>People usually eat at least two sushi meals.</b>

346
00:22:07,443 --> 00:22:09,840
<b>No way. People usually eat one.</b>

347
00:22:09,845 --> 00:22:11,610
<b>That's why it's called one serving.</b>

348
00:22:11,613 --> 00:22:13,675
<b>You eat a lot. That's what.</b>

349
00:22:14,149 --> 00:22:15,150
<b>Yes.</b>

350
00:22:15,150 --> 00:22:18,150
<b>Anyway, isn't something weird about the three of them?</b>

351
00:22:18,153 --> 00:22:20,445
<b>No. Not at all.</b>

352
00:22:20,522 --> 00:22:22,350
<b>Stop minding that table.</b>

353
00:22:22,358 --> 00:22:24,885
<b>It's none of your business.</b>

354
00:22:27,563 --> 00:22:29,530
<b>It really is a small world.</b>

355
00:22:29,531 --> 00:22:32,495
<b>I never imagined that you two would be friends.</b>

356
00:22:34,436 --> 00:22:37,740
<b>Anchor Lee, I told you before...</b>

357
00:22:37,740 --> 00:22:39,270
<b>that...</b>

358
00:22:39,274 --> 00:22:42,205
<b>there was a problem with my memory.</b>

359
00:22:43,512 --> 00:22:47,575
<b>Doctor Yoo was actually my counselor for about two years.</b>

360
00:22:47,950 --> 00:22:51,845
<b>Then we lost contact as I went into acting.</b>

361
00:22:52,087 --> 00:22:55,385
<b>It wouldn't be good if people found out I was counseled.</b>

362
00:22:55,657 --> 00:22:57,255
<b>I see.</b>

363
00:22:57,726 --> 00:23:00,820
<b>It's shocking to think that it had been five years already.</b>

364
00:23:00,829 --> 00:23:02,555
<b>Isn't that so, Doctor Yoo?</b>

365
00:23:02,564 --> 00:23:04,125
<b>You're right.</b>

366
00:23:04,967 --> 00:23:08,130
<b>But you two seem like an unlikely match.</b>

367
00:23:08,137 --> 00:23:10,335
<b>Since when were you two friends?</b>

368
00:23:13,542 --> 00:23:16,740
<b>For a long time. Since when we were 11.</b>

369
00:23:16,745 --> 00:23:19,875
<b>Yes, it's a pretty gross relationship.</b>

370
00:23:20,816 --> 00:23:23,075
<b>You two must be very close.</b>

371
00:23:23,419 --> 00:23:24,750
<b>Oh, right.</b>

372
00:23:24,753 --> 00:23:28,385
<b>Anchor Lee, may I have a word with you after we eat?</b>

373
00:23:29,258 --> 00:23:30,855
<b>Sure.</b>

374
00:23:33,529 --> 00:23:36,425
<b>I've been here once for a production presentation.</b>

375
00:23:37,166 --> 00:23:40,365
<b>It's kind of strange to see how quiet it is.</b>

376
00:23:41,804 --> 00:23:45,865
<b>There aren't a lot of places in our building where we can have privacy.</b>

377
00:23:56,018 --> 00:23:58,350
<b>I didn't know...</b>

378
00:23:58,353 --> 00:24:02,185
<b>what to say or how I should face you when I ran into you again.</b>

379
00:24:07,563 --> 00:24:09,725
<b>Did you already know...</b>

380
00:24:11,033 --> 00:24:13,765
<b>that I had a problem with my memory?</b>

381
00:24:17,206 --> 00:24:20,205
<b>And that I had Doctor Yoo as a counselor?</b>

382
00:24:21,109 --> 00:24:22,935
<b>Did you know?</b>

383
00:24:25,547 --> 00:24:27,105
<b>Yes.</b>

384
00:24:37,326 --> 00:24:39,390
<b>Was that why you were so good to me?</b>

385
00:24:39,394 --> 00:24:41,285
<b>Did you pity me?</b>

386
00:24:41,797 --> 00:24:42,890
<b>No.</b>

387
00:24:42,898 --> 00:24:44,730
<b>You pitied me, didn't you?</b>

388
00:24:44,733 --> 00:24:46,665
<b>I never pitied you.</b>

389
00:24:48,070 --> 00:24:50,935
<b>I'm not in a position to pity anyone,</b>

390
00:24:51,406 --> 00:24:54,265
<b>and there's no reason for you to be pitied.</b>

391
00:24:56,378 --> 00:24:58,205
<b>You are very difficult,</b>

392
00:24:58,447 --> 00:25:00,105
<b>Anchor Lee.</b>

393
00:25:04,920 --> 00:25:07,920
<b>You always seem to tell the truth,</b>

394
00:25:07,923 --> 00:25:10,385
<b>yet it doesn't seem like the truth.</b>

395
00:25:11,159 --> 00:25:13,755
<b>I hear a lot from you,</b>

396
00:25:13,896 --> 00:25:16,225
<b>but it seems like I heard nothing.</b>

397
00:25:17,332 --> 00:25:19,495
<b>It's frustrating at times,</b>

398
00:25:21,069 --> 00:25:23,065
<b>but I keep wanting to know more.</b>

399
00:25:25,140 --> 00:25:27,065
<b>I find you very difficult,</b>

400
00:25:29,144 --> 00:25:30,835
<b>Anchor Lee.</b>

401
00:25:52,935 --> 00:25:54,030
<b>Hello?</b>

402
00:25:54,036 --> 00:25:57,195
<b>Doctor Yoo, this is Yeo Ha Jin.</b>

403
00:25:57,472 --> 00:25:59,705
<b>You haven't changed your number.</b>

404
00:26:02,811 --> 00:26:05,940
<b>This place is still the same.</b>

405
00:26:05,948 --> 00:26:07,640
<b>And it's still empty.</b>

406
00:26:07,649 --> 00:26:09,510
<b>There are a lot of customers during lunchtime.</b>

407
00:26:09,518 --> 00:26:11,115
<b>I see.</b>

408
00:26:12,554 --> 00:26:14,750
<b>You're still the same too, Doctor Yoo.</b>

409
00:26:14,756 --> 00:26:16,755
<b>You haven't gotten old at all.</b>

410
00:26:16,925 --> 00:26:20,460
<b>Wouldn't it be heartbreaking if I grew noticeably old in five years?</b>

411
00:26:20,462 --> 00:26:22,195
<b>Is that so?</b>

412
00:26:22,464 --> 00:26:24,730
<b>It's really great to see you again.</b>

413
00:26:24,733 --> 00:26:28,065
<b>I was too shocked before to celebrate our reunion.</b>

414
00:26:28,637 --> 00:26:31,070
<b>- Hello. What would you like? - Hello.</b>

415
00:26:31,073 --> 00:26:32,240
<b>Two bowls of rice soup, please.</b>

416
00:26:32,240 --> 00:26:34,105
<b>- Okay. - Yes.</b>

417
00:26:34,409 --> 00:26:38,645
<b>Right, what did Anchor Lee say about me?</b>

418
00:26:38,847 --> 00:26:41,445
<b>I'm sure you two talk a lot since you're friends.</b>

419
00:26:41,717 --> 00:26:44,475
<b>Well, I don't know.</b>

420
00:26:44,786 --> 00:26:47,415
<b>I'm guessing it wasn't anything great.</b>

421
00:26:49,625 --> 00:26:51,285
<b>To be honest,</b>

422
00:26:51,627 --> 00:26:54,485
<b>I like him a lot.</b>

423
00:26:55,697 --> 00:26:58,155
<b>But he won't accept my feelings.</b>

424
00:26:59,801 --> 00:27:02,195
<b>It feels unfair to have him push me away...</b>

425
00:27:02,371 --> 00:27:05,465
<b>after he confuses me by leading me on.</b>

426
00:27:05,507 --> 00:27:08,735
<b>I've always wondered why he acted like that.</b>

427
00:27:09,311 --> 00:27:11,675
<b>But I think I kind of get it...</b>

428
00:27:12,748 --> 00:27:14,605
<b>thanks to you.</b>

429
00:27:15,484 --> 00:27:17,080
<b>What do you mean?</b>

430
00:27:17,085 --> 00:27:19,945
<b>You once told me...</b>

431
00:27:20,389 --> 00:27:25,585
<b>that your best friend has a disease where he can't forget anything.</b>

432
00:27:28,830 --> 00:27:32,165
<b>I had so much fun and was very happy.</b>

433
00:27:33,602 --> 00:27:36,695
<b>I remember those feelings vividly.</b>

434
00:27:36,872 --> 00:27:38,605
<b>But I have...</b>

435
00:27:39,074 --> 00:27:42,205
<b>no idea who I was with at that time.</b>

436
00:27:43,178 --> 00:27:45,210
<b>It definitely wasn't Ha Kyung.</b>

437
00:27:45,213 --> 00:27:47,740
<b>There's no need to remember everything.</b>

438
00:27:47,749 --> 00:27:49,880
<b>People all forget and move on.</b>

439
00:27:49,885 --> 00:27:51,815
<b>That's normal.</b>

440
00:27:52,421 --> 00:27:54,585
<b>This is normal?</b>

441
00:27:54,856 --> 00:27:58,885
<b>I know one person who isn't like that.</b>

442
00:27:58,994 --> 00:28:03,895
<b>He's my best friend since when we were 11.</b>

443
00:28:04,599 --> 00:28:08,565
<b>He can't forget anything.</b>

444
00:28:09,204 --> 00:28:10,330
<b>Why not?</b>

445
00:28:10,338 --> 00:28:12,105
<b>Because of a disease.</b>

446
00:28:12,641 --> 00:28:14,535
<b>A disease that won't let him forget.</b>

447
00:28:21,249 --> 00:28:24,615
<b>I can tell by your face that I must be right.</b>

448
00:28:25,387 --> 00:28:27,245
<b>I thought so.</b>

449
00:28:27,756 --> 00:28:30,050
<b>Anchor Lee often said...</b>

450
00:28:30,058 --> 00:28:32,485
<b>he has too good of a memory.</b>

451
00:28:32,728 --> 00:28:36,590
<b>- That's... Did I... - I heard many things from you...</b>

452
00:28:36,598 --> 00:28:39,125
<b>when I was counseled,</b>

453
00:28:40,068 --> 00:28:43,995
<b>but I could never forget what you said about your friend.</b>

454
00:28:45,507 --> 00:28:48,405
<b>I guess it's because that sounded very special to me.</b>

455
00:28:51,480 --> 00:28:54,105
<b>It feels like I finally resolved my riddle.</b>

456
00:28:56,451 --> 00:28:59,315
<b>Did you say it was hyperthymesia?</b>

457
00:29:01,523 --> 00:29:03,355
<b>The name of that disease.</b>

458
00:29:04,626 --> 00:29:05,620
<b>(Hyperthymesia)</b>

459
00:29:05,627 --> 00:29:06,960
<b>Reporter Choi Yul.</b>

460
00:29:06,962 --> 00:29:09,160
<b>I heard people who were arrested...</b>

461
00:29:09,164 --> 00:29:11,530
<b>for using violent language and behavior...</b>

462
